  "prompt": "How do you see a deleted comment on instagram?",
  "response": "Once a comment is deleted on Instagram, it cannot be retrieved through the app as there is no built-in feature to view deleted comments. However, there are a couple of options to consider if you want to track or recall comments:\n\n1. **Notifications**: If you received a notification for the comment before it was deleted, you might check your notifications (if you're quick enough) to see the history of comments.\n\n2. **Screenshots**: If you, or someone else, took a screenshot of the comment before it was deleted, that would be your only way to see the content of the deleted comment.\n\n3. **Third-party apps**: Some third-party applications claim to provide additional functionality for social media, including tracking comments, but be cautious with these as they may violate Instagram's terms of service or compromise your privacy.\n\n4. **Ask the person**: If the comment was from someone you know, you could ask them if they remember what they wrote.\n\nUltimately, once a comment is deleted, it is permanently removed from the platform, and there is no official way to recover it.",
